Installation:
	1) Install all the required libraries (QT and opengl).
	2) Move to src directory (>>cd [path-to-src])
	3) Compile (>>make all)
	4) Run (>>./Assignment4 trashcan.ply cube2.ply street_lamp.ply)

Scene Description:
	1) A robot is moving in a park like environment.
	2) There is drone fly independently of the robot in the park.
	3) When robot calls (user presses button) it, the drone comes and sit on the robot.
	4) Scene Graph: Root -> (robot body, drone) ; Robot body -> (Head, 2 x arms, 2 x legs)

User Interaction options:

	ZOOM-IN/OUT  					----- GUI Slider
	ROTATE   							----- Mouse Left key + drag
	Translate							----- GUI Slider
	Toggle Lights 				----- GUI checkbox
	Toggle Bounding Box	 	----- GUI checkbox
	Toggle Texture 				----- GUI checkbox
	Change Texture 				----- GUI push button
	Robot/Drone Speed			----- GUI Sliders
	Toggle Camera					----- GUI Push button
	Attach flying object	----- GUI checkbox
	Exit          				----- esc
	

Program Features:

	1) Program implements a scene graph from the scratch and thoroughly follows it properties.
	2) Entire program is built using MVC architecture.
	3) A graphical user interface is provided for easy user interaction using QT.
	4) The program can handle any given .ply files and textures once files are named accordingly.

